public enum Datatype
extends java.lang.Enum<Datatype>

Supported datatypes in the Information Workbench. These datatypes (mostly XSD + RDFS) are used especially in the TripleEditorWidget for type selection of the input values.

as

getLabel

public static java.lang.String getLabel(org.openrdf.model.URI typeURI)
Return a string representation for the given type URI, which corresponds to the label of the given resource as retrieved via ReadWriteDataManager#getLabel(). This method implements a special case for type URIs rdfs:Resource (=> URI/Resource) and rdfs:Literal (=> Literal (any/untyped)).
